annotation: usually NIM

annotation: NIM

annotation: coord IM with disease /ther (IM), not /drug ther

annotation: do not confuse with HYPERGLYCINEMIA, NONKETOTIC

annotation: general; prefer specifics

name: Hypersensitivity

annotation: do not routinely index also under RENAL ARTERY or RENAL ARTERY OBSTRUCTION

annotation: GEN; NIM; no qualif when NIM coord; SALINE SOLUTION, HYPERTONIC & GLUCOSE SOLUTION, HYPERTONIC are available; DF: HYPOTONIC SOL

annotation: /defic = IMMUNOGLOBULIN D / defic + DYSGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM); gammopathy: coordinate IMMUNOGLOBULIN D (IM) with PARAPROTEINEMIAS (IM) but consider also HYPERGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM), follow text;

name: Immunoglobulin E
annotation: /defic = IMMUNOGLOBULIN E / defic + DYSGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM); gammopathy: coordinate IMMUNOGLOBULIN E (IM) with PARAPROTEINEMIAS (IM) but consider also HYPERGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM), follow text;

name: Immunoglobulin G
annotation: gammopathy: coordinate IMMUNOGLOBULIN G (IM) with PARAPROTEINEMIAS (IM) but consider also HYPERGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA, follow text

name: Immunoglobulin M
annotation: /defic = IMMUNOGLOBULIN M / defic + DYSGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM); gammopathy: coordinate IMMUNOGLOBULIN M (IM) with PARAPROTEINEMIAS (IM) but consider also HYPERGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM), follow text;

name: Ileal Diseases

name: Illegitimacy

name: Illinois
annotation: CHICAGO is also available

name: Illusions
annotation: do not confuse with DELUSIONS

name: Image Enhancement
annotation: RADIOGRAPHIC IMAGE ENHANCEMENT is also available

name: Image Processing, Computer-Assisted

name: Imagination

name: Imides
annotation: do not confuse with IMINES or AMIDES

name: Imines
annotation: do not confuse with IMIDES or AMINES

name: Imino Acids
annotation: do not confuse with AMINO ACIDS

name: Imitative Behavior
annotation: human & animal

name: Immobilization

name: Immune System
annotation: GEN: prefer specifics; /physiol: consider also IMMUNITY & its indentions

name: Immune Tolerance

name: Immunity

name: Immunity, Active
annotation: coordinate with specific disease / immunol

name: Immunity, Cellular
annotation: coordinate with specific disease / immunol

name: Immunity, Maternally-Acquired
annotation: of fetus by transplacental transfer or of neonate through colostrum or milk; do not add MATERNAL-FETAL EXCHANGE; note category: do not confuse with IMMUNIZATION, PASSIVE (Cat E); TN 242

name: Immunity, Innate

name: Immunization, Passive
annotation: IM; note category: do not confuse with IMMUNITY, MATERNALLY-ACQUIRED (Cat G) nor X ref PASSIVE TRANSFER OF IMMUNITY with passive transfer of immune tolerance ( = IMMUNOSUPPRESSION) nor X ref IMMUNOGLOBULIN THERAPY with IMMUNOGLOBULINS, INTRAVENOUS

name: Immunoassay
annotation: general or unspecified; prefer specifics; usually NIM

name: Immunochemistry

name: Immunoelectrophoresis
annotation: GEN or unspecified; prefer specifics; NIM

name: Immunoelectrophoresis, Two-Dimensional
annotation: usually NIM; do not confuse entry term IMMUNOELECTROPHORESIS, CROSSED with IMMUNOELECTROPHORESIS, CROSSOVER see COUNTERIMMUNOELECTROPHORESIS

name: Immunoenzyme Techniques

name: Immunogenetics

name: Immunoglobulin Allotypes
annotation: general or unspecified; prefer specifics; Am allotype goes here (IM) + IMMUNOGLOBULIN A (IM); DF: IG ALLOTYPES

name: Immunoglobulins
annotation: general: prefer specifics; /admin: consider also IMMUNOGLOBULINS, INTRAVENOUS; /defic permitted but consider also IMMUNOLOGIC DEFICIENCY SYNDROMES ; /ther use: consider also IMMUNOGLOBULIN THERAPY see IMMUNIZATION, PASSIVE; allotypes = IMMUNOGLOBULIN ALLOTYPES or specifics

name: Immunoglobulin alpha-Chains

name: Immunoglobulin delta-Chains
annotation: gammopathy: coordinate IMMUNOGLOBULIN DELTA-CHAINS (IM) with PARAPROTEINEMIAS (IM) but consider also HYPERGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM) or HEAVY CHAIN DISEASE (IM), follow text; DF: IG DELTA CHAIN

name: Immunoglobulin epsilon-Chains
annotation: gammopathy: coordinate IMMUNOGLOBULIN EPSILON-CHAINS (IM) with PARAPROTEINEMIAS (IM) but consider also HYPERGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM) or HEAVY CHAIN DISEASE (IM), follow text; DF: IG EPSILON CHAIN

name: Immunoglobulin gamma-Chains
annotation: gammopathy: coordinate IMMUNOGLOBULIN GAMMA-CHAINS (IM) with PARAPROTEINEMIAS (IM) but consider also HYPERGAMMAGLOBULINEMIA (IM) or HEAVY CHAIN DISEASE (IM), follow text; DF: IG GAMMA CHAIN

name: Immunoglobulin Heavy Chains

annotation: add UNITED STATES; research support by this agency is checked as RESEARCH SUPPORT, N.I.H., EXTRAMURAL or RESEARCH SUPPORT, N.I.H., INTRAMURAL; CATALOGER: Use NAF entry

name: Necatoriasis
annotation: hookworm infect; human & animal

name: Necrobiosis Lipoidica
annotation: note entry term NECROBIOSIS LIPOIDICA DIABETICORUM: do not index also under DIABETES MELLITUS unless particularly discussed

name: Necrosis
annotation: IM for general or for necrotic process; necrosis in an organ or tissue: index organ or tissue /pathol  + NECROSIS (NIM); note specific necrosis terms; radionecrosis: index RADIATION INJURIES /pathol + organ /pathol + NECROSIS (NIM)

name: Necturus
annotation: NIM when experimental animal

name: Necturus maculosus
annotation: NIM when experimental animal

annotation: infection = GONORRHEA

annotation: specific serogroups are also available; infection: probably MENINGITIS, MENINGOCOCCAL or, if not meningitis, MENINGOCOCCAL INFECTIONS

name: Nematoda
annotation: general or unspecified; prefer specifics; infection = NEMATODE INFECTIONS; coordinate with specific precoordinated helminth terms (ANTIGENS, HELMINTH, etc) if pertinent

annotation: GEN only: prefer specifics; /drug ther: consider also ANTINEMATODAL AGENTS

name: Nematospiroides dubius
annotation: a species of nematode; infection: coord IM with STRONGYLIDA INFECTIONS (IM); for antigens, coord with ANTIGENS, HELMINTH, for antibodies, coord with ANTIBODIES, HELMINTH

name: Neonatal Abstinence Syndrome

name: Congenital, Hereditary, and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities
annotation: used for searching; INDEXER: Do not use; CATALOGER: Do not use

annotation: IM general only or for invasive process; coordinate NIM with specific neoplasm terms / pathol (IM)

name: Neoplasm Proteins

annotation: IM; differentiate from NEOPLASMS, MULTIPLE PRIMARY and NEOPLASMS, SECOND PRIMARY; do not confuse with NEOPLASM, RESIDUAL

annotation: IM; must be spontaneous: for regression or remission after ther, use REMISSION INDUCTION; Manual 24.4.1.9; DF: NEOPL REGRESSION SPONTANEOUS

annotation: includes seeding by surgery biopsy, palpation, etc.

annotation: IM general only; coordinate NIM with no qualifiers with neoplasm terms /diag, /diag image and/or /pathol; do not confuse with NEOPLASM GRADING; staging is given in Roman numerals, grading in Arabic numerals

name: Neoplasms
annotation: general; prefer specifics; familial: consider also NEOPLASTIC SYNDROMES, HEREDITARY; metastatic cancer of unknown origin: index NEOPLASM METASTASIS

name: Neoplasms by Histologic Type
annotation: used for searching; INDEXER: Do not use; CATALOGER: Do not use

name: Neoplasms by Site
annotation: used for searching; INDEXER: Do not use; CATALOGER: Do not use

name: Neoplasms, Connective Tissue
annotation: neoplasms composed of connective tissue, NOT neoplasms located in connective tissue: coordinate with precoordinated organ/neoplasm term

name: Neoplasms, Germ Cell and Embryonal
annotation: neoplasms composed of germ cells or embryonic tissue, NOT neoplasms located in germ cells or embryonic tissue; coordinate with precoordinated organ/neoplasm term

name: Neoplasms, Experimental
annotation: IM general only; not a routine coordinate for specific neoplasms in experimental animals; policy: Manual 24.5+; /chem ind: Manual 24.5.6+; spontaneous: Manual 24.5.5; DF: NEOPL EXPER

annotation: neoplasms composed of glandular & epithelial tissue, NOT neoplasms located in various glands or epithelium; coordinate with precoordinated organ/neoplasm term

annotation: neoplasms composed of muscle tissue, NOT neoplasms located in muscles; coord IM with precoord organ/neopl term (IM)

annotation: IM; coord with specific histol type (IM) + organ/neopl term (IM); Manual 24.4.3.2+; DF: NEOPL RAD IND

name: Neoplasms, Unknown Primary
annotation: IM; do not use /second; coord IM with organ/neopl term with /second (IM) + histol type /second (IM); Manual 24.4.1.8

name: Neoplastic Processes
annotation: general or unspecified; prefer specifics

name: Neoplastic Syndromes, Hereditary

name: Nephritis
annotation: familial: consider also NEPHRITIS, HEREDITARY

annotation: do not confuse with MOTOR ENDPLATE

name: Nerve Growth Factors
annotation: NERVE GROWTH FACTOR is also available

name: Nerve Net

name: Nerve Regeneration
annotation: coordinate with specific nerve /physiol not /growth

name: Nerve Tissue

name: Nervous System Physiological Phenomena
annotation: general or unspecified; prefer specifics

name: Nesting Behavior
annotation: animal only

annotation: do not confuse entry term SPINAL CORD MYELODYSPLASIA with MYELODYSPLASTIC SYNDROMES, a defect of bone marrow formation

name: Neuralgia
annotation: coordinate IM with specific nerve (IM) if pertinent

annotation: remember also NEUROCIRCULATORY ASTHENIA exists

name: Neurilemmoma
annotation: benign or malignant; coordinate IM with precoordinated organ/neoplasm term (IM)

name: Neuroanatomy
annotation: use for the discipline only; not for NERVOUS SYSTEM /anat

name: Neurobiology

name: Neuroblastoma

name: Neurochemistry
annotation: the discipline only (education, history, etc); for the chemistry of the nervous system, use the qualifier /chem with NERVOUS SYSTEM or specific nervous system component

name: Neurocirculatory Asthenia
annotation: remember NEURASTHENIA also exists

name: Neurodermatitis
annotation: eczematous skin dis with intense itching

name: Neuroeffector Junction
annotation: a synapse between a neuron & an effector cell

name: Neuroendocrinology

name: Neurofibrils
annotation: do not confuse with NERVE FIBERS

name: Neurofibroma

name: Neurofibromatosis 1
annotation: do not confuse with NEUROFIBROMATOSIS 2; coord IM with precoord organ/neopl term (IM) if relevant

name: Neuroleptic Malignant Syndrome

name: Neurologic Manifestations
annotation: not used for indexing since 1989; prior to 1989 used for neurol manifest of non-neural diseases

name: Neuroma
annotation: coordinate with precoordinated organ/neoplasm term

name: Neuromuscular Agents

name: Neuromuscular Blocking Agents

name: Neuromuscular Diseases

name: Neurons
annotation: do not use as a substitute or synonym for BRAIN /cytol

name: Neurons, Afferent
annotation: do not confuse with NEURONS, EFFERENT which activate muscle and secretory cells

name: Neurons, Efferent
annotation: do not confuse with NEURONS, AFFERENT which are sensory neurons

name: Hereditary Sensory and Autonomic Neuropathies

name: Neuropeptide Y
annotation: a neurotransmitter; /biosyn /physiol permitted

name: Neuropeptides
annotation: GEN or unspecified; prefer specifics

name: Neuropharmacology
annotation: a branch of pharmacology; not for NERVOUS SYSTEM /drug eff

name: Neurophysiology
annotation: SPEC only: not for NERVOUS SYSTEM PHYSIOLOGY;DF: NEUROPHYSIOL

name: Neuropsychology
annotation: SPEC: not for coord of NERVOUS SYSTEM DISEASES /psychol; IM, SPEC qualif; NIM coord, no qualif; DF: NEUROPSYCHOL

name: Neuroradiography
annotation: IM general only; avoid as NIM coordinate with terms treed under CENTRAL NERVOUS SYSTEM with /diag image; instead prefer specific radiographic technique

name: Neurosciences
annotation: use for the discipline only (education, history, etc) only

name: Neurosecretory Systems
annotation: /physiol: consider also NEUROSECRETION

name: Neurospora
annotation: an ascomycete much used in genetic & enzyme research; do not confuse with NEOSPORA, a protozoon

name: Neurospora crassa
annotation: do not confuse with NEOSPORA, a protozoan

name: Neurotensin

name: Neurotoxins

name: Neutron Activation Analysis
annotation: usually NIM

name: Neutrons
annotation: elementary particles; IM; FAST NEUTRONS is available

name: Neutrophils
annotation: decrease in number = NEUTROPENIA; neutrophil chemotaxis: coordinate with CHEMOTAXIS, LEUKOCYTE; note entry term LE CELLS: do not coordinate with LUPUS ERYTHEMATOSUS, SYSTEMIC unless disease is particularly discussed

name: Nevus
annotation: coordinate IM with SKIN NEOPLASMS (IM) + site (IM or NIM) if relevant; general; note many specific nevus terms

name: Nevus of Ota
annotation: coordinate with SKIN NEOPLASMS + site if relevant

name: Nevus, Pigmented
annotation: coordinate with SKIN NEOPLASMS + site if relevant

name: New Brunswick
annotation: a province of eastern Canada

name: New Caledonia
annotation: an island group in Melanesia

name: New England
annotation: index specific states as needed but use NEW ENGLAND when text uses the term & when the region is the intent of the author; CATALOGER: Use for 4 or more states

name: New Guinea

name: Vanuatu
annotation: an island group in Melanesia; X ref NEW HEBRIDES was its former name

name: New South Wales
annotation: a state of Australia

name: New York
annotation: NEW YORK CITY is also available

name: New Zealand

annotation: /defic: consider also PELLAGRA; /ther use: coordinate disease with /drug ther, not /diet ther

name: Niemann-Pick Diseases
annotation: note specific types are available

name: Nigeria
annotation: do not confuse with NIGER, another western Africa republic to its north; Biafra goes here

name: Night Care
annotation: institutional care only

name: Niobium
annotation: synonym: Columbium (Cb)

name: Nipples

annotation: general; prefer specifics; do not confuse with NITRITE REDUCTASES

name: Nitrates

name: Nitrogen Mustard Compounds
annotation: do not confuse with NITROGEN MUSTARD, a specific chemical

name: Nitroreductases
annotation: general; prefer specifics

name: Nitrosamines
annotation: carcinogens

name: Nitrous Acid
annotation: do not confuse with NITRIC ACID

name: Nobel Prize
annotation: award for medicine: coordinate with specific field or specialty but not with MEDICINE

name: Nocardia
annotation: infection = NOCARDIA INFECTIONS

name: Nocardia asteroides
annotation: infection: coord IM with NOCARDIA INFECTIONS (IM)

name: Nocardia Infections
annotation: gram-pos bact infect

name: Nocardiaceae
annotation: in soil, animals & man

name: Nodose Ganglion
